WEBVTT

00:00.800 --> 00:02.800
☺ Subbed By BARFNUTS ☺

00:03.000 --> 00:05.880
[wind whistles]

00:06.963 --> 00:09.032
[groans]

00:09.316 --> 00:10.292
Huh?

00:10.330 --> 00:11.782
<i>HATRED:
Good morning.</i>

00:11.911 --> 00:13.137
<i>Last night I drugged you boys</i>

00:13.221 --> 00:15.932
<i>and had H.E.L.P.Er. take you
to your new homes.</i>

00:16.015 --> 00:18.809
<i>As your bodyguard, I must
prepare you for the worst.</i>

00:18.893 --> 00:20.978
<i>Your father
is most likely dead.</i>

00:21.062 --> 00:23.147
<i>He was crushed to death
by a disco ball,</i>

00:23.231 --> 00:26.526
<i>And his lifeless husk was
taken by The Monarch.</i>

00:26.609 --> 00:29.445
<i>Your godfathers have the rest
of the info.</i>

00:29.529 --> 00:32.323
GENTLEMAN:
Get in, son. Welcome to Tangier.

00:32.406 --> 00:36.160
<i>They will raise you as their
own sons from here on out.</i>

00:36.244 --> 00:38.746
<i>After! write these notes,
I plan on shooting myself,</i>

00:38.829 --> 00:41.040
<i>then burning
the Venture estate down.</i>

00:41.123 --> 00:43.751
<i>Not really, but, again,
that would be the worst,</i>

00:43.834 --> 00:46.295
<i>and I want to prepare you
for the worst,</i>

00:46.379 --> 00:47.588
<i>'cause I love you both.</i>

00:47.672 --> 00:49.257
<i>Uncle Vatred.</i>

00:49.340 --> 00:50.841
Oh, good.
You're up. Here.

00:50.925 --> 00:53.219
Put this on and meet me
out back.

00:53.302 --> 00:55.555
Oh, and, uh, welcome
to Boca Raton.

00:55.638 --> 00:57.431
[chuckles]
Son.

01:00.977 --> 01:02.562
ACTION MAN:
Poor little guy.

01:02.645 --> 01:04.313
HANK:
ls that your... pet?

01:04.397 --> 01:05.898
Blackie died 15 years ago.

01:05.982 --> 01:08.776
That's Entmann -- first of
Team Venture to go.

01:08.859 --> 01:10.695
Gosh, I'm awful sorry.

01:10.778 --> 01:13.614
"You are my pal, and you are
my friend.

01:13.698 --> 01:16.492
And your weird body,
to heaven, I send.

01:16.576 --> 01:18.703
When you were massive
and full of size,

01:18.786 --> 01:21.622
you gave me council,
because you were wise.

01:21.706 --> 01:24.083
Saying, 'Action Man,
take it down a notch.

01:24.166 --> 01:27.336
Stop just thinking
with your Action crotch.'

01:27.420 --> 01:29.880
And when you were shrunk down
to a little mole,

01:29.964 --> 01:32.633
you were able to
swim laps in a little bowl.

01:32.717 --> 01:35.803
Now you are dead
'cause of my chair.

01:35.886 --> 01:38.264
I had no idea that
you were there.

01:38.347 --> 01:41.225
When I rocked back in repose,

01:41.309 --> 01:44.353
you died and began
to decompose."

01:44.437 --> 01:45.521
[ sniffles ]

01:45.605 --> 01:47.565
[zip]

01:47.648 --> 01:49.942
Dude!
What are you doing?!

01:50.026 --> 01:51.944
Venture tradition, son.
[Zip 1

01:52.028 --> 01:53.321
Oh. Uh, should I--

01:53.404 --> 01:54.822
Nope.
You're the youngest here.

01:54.905 --> 01:57.408
You got to fertilize the ground
to represent new life.

01:57.491 --> 01:59.410
Drop 'em and squat.

01:59.493 --> 02:02.079
Now, now, son. That's not
a napkin, that's bread.

02:02.163 --> 02:04.248
You scoop up your couscous
With it.

02:04.332 --> 02:06.250
Sorry. I'm used
to bread-shaped bread.

02:06.334 --> 02:08.252
Don't drink that.
Dysentery.

02:08.336 --> 02:11.172
You'll be crapping your brains
out all over my antiques.

02:11.255 --> 02:12.840
You'll learn the customs here
in no time.

02:12.923 --> 02:14.550
I hope I don't have to.

02:14.634 --> 02:16.802
I really think my dad's okay,
Mr. Gentleman.

02:16.886 --> 02:19.555
"Mr. Gentleman"?
You call me Pop-Pop.

02:19.639 --> 02:21.974
Rebuilding Team Venture,
old man?

02:22.058 --> 02:24.352
Or just found yourself
a new plaything?

02:24.435 --> 02:26.437
Hey, you remember me,
do you, laddie?

02:26.520 --> 02:29.482
So, you might want to show me
a little more respect.

02:29.565 --> 02:31.609
Respect?
You clowns were a joke

02:31.692 --> 02:33.986
even before the Action Man
went to rehab.

02:34.070 --> 02:36.489
Sorry, the old ears don't
hear so good anymore.

02:36.572 --> 02:38.449
What was that?
- You heard me.

02:38.532 --> 02:41.661
Dean, be a good boy and go
pick a song on the jukebox.

02:41.744 --> 02:44.288
This man wants to dance
with your Pop-Pop.

02:44.372 --> 02:45.456
Okay.

02:45.539 --> 02:47.750
He's a little young...
even for you.

02:47.833 --> 02:49.460
Are you sure you want to have
a fight?

02:49.543 --> 02:51.212
'Cause I'm only go use
a thumb.

02:51.295 --> 02:53.005
Uh... the left one.

02:53.089 --> 02:54.840
The right one's
too powerful for you.

02:54.924 --> 02:58.219
I'd love to see that.

02:58.302 --> 03:01.305
[yells]

03:01.389 --> 03:02.473
[breathing shakily]

03:02.556 --> 03:04.934
I didn't specify my thumb.

03:06.811 --> 03:09.355
[rustling ]

03:09.438 --> 03:12.358
I know you're there.
You move, and I shoot.

03:12.441 --> 03:13.484
Oh, no, Gary.

03:13.567 --> 03:15.695
Please don't shoot me
with your stick.

03:15.778 --> 03:16.862
Eh, it's all I --

03:16.946 --> 03:18.698
Yeah, blah, blah.
Look, I need your help.

03:18.781 --> 03:20.032
How'd you find me?

03:20.116 --> 03:21.867
Idiot, you're camping
on our property.

03:21.951 --> 03:24.370
How dumb do you think I am?
- Uh, very?

03:24.453 --> 03:26.330
Yeah, I'd love to keep
playing this game with you,

03:26.414 --> 03:27.873
but we got problems.

03:27.957 --> 03:30.668
The Monarch has Doc.
- How did that happen?

03:30.751 --> 03:32.837
Doc crashed a party
at Don Hell's.

03:32.920 --> 03:34.463
Whoa!
Not smart.

03:34.547 --> 03:36.841
Villain nightclub.
Bad people in there.

03:36.924 --> 03:39.093
So, are you in?
I know it's touchy for you,

03:39.176 --> 03:40.803
and you'll probably baby out
on me,

03:40.886 --> 03:42.680
but I also know that you're
a good man...

03:42.763 --> 03:44.181
under all that pudge.

03:44.265 --> 03:45.808
Yeah, I'm pudgy.
And you're wearing

03:45.891 --> 03:48.561
a bulletproof vest made from
an old couch, I assume.

03:48.644 --> 03:50.646
Yeah, I'm in.
Let's bring him home.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.481
[mimics gun cock]

03:52.565 --> 03:54.150
Did you just cock your stick?

03:54.233 --> 03:56.026
Yeah. Whatever.
So, I just -- so, what?

03:56.110 --> 03:58.821
So, you ready?
I am gonna wet myself.

03:58.904 --> 04:01.157
MRS. MONARCH:
Calm down! I'm almost done.

04:01.240 --> 04:02.825
Hey, what about
putting him in the one

04:02.908 --> 04:05.411
with a hungry rat in a cage
that he wears as a mask?

04:05.494 --> 04:07.037
It'll eat his nose.

04:07.121 --> 04:08.372
MRS. MONARCH:
I told you -- rats, piranhas,

04:08.456 --> 04:10.541
sharks, and badgers are
too much hassle.

04:10.624 --> 04:12.835
No animals.
- Okay!

04:12.918 --> 04:15.171
Hey, what about just
straight-up flaying, huh?

04:15.254 --> 04:18.173
But as a sinister twist --
ice knife?

04:18.257 --> 04:19.841
Oh, put that one down.

04:19.925 --> 04:21.385
Just wait for me to finish.

04:21.469 --> 04:24.054
I can't wait.
I'm so excited!

04:24.138 --> 04:25.806
All right.
All right, all right.

04:25.890 --> 04:27.808
Calm down, now.
Work on the old list.

04:27.892 --> 04:30.436
Nifty, nifty little listy.

04:30.519 --> 04:32.897
Number 15 -- ice knife.

04:32.980 --> 04:35.191
[sighs]
Okay, I'm calm now.

04:35.274 --> 04:37.526
Everything's cool.
- Good.

04:37.610 --> 04:40.988
Broken glass in ears,
question mark.

04:41.071 --> 04:42.740
I just peed myself
a little.

04:42.823 --> 04:44.992
Sweetie, please, relax.

04:45.075 --> 04:46.410
I really
appreciate this.

04:46.494 --> 04:48.412
I'm only doing it 'cause it's
against Guild regulations

04:48.496 --> 04:50.748
to torture somebody
with an unattended injury.

04:50.831 --> 04:53.542
Yeah, not buying it.
I know you're the softie here.

04:53.626 --> 04:55.544
Not my first time
at the rodeo.

04:55.628 --> 04:57.421
Rodeo's over, baldy.
You're hog-tied.

04:57.505 --> 04:59.048
I'm just waiting
for my husband

04:59.131 --> 05:01.091
to pick out a barbecue sauce
to spread on you.

05:01.175 --> 05:04.094
- Ow!
- Yeah, dislocated. Figured.

05:04.178 --> 05:07.097
[sighs]
I know you clowns aren't gonna do anything.

05:07.181 --> 05:08.891
You never do.

05:08.974 --> 05:11.018
Yeah, he may not be very good
at it, but he loves it,

05:11.101 --> 05:13.437
and I love him, so you
better play along.

05:13.521 --> 05:15.064
How about you
pop my hip back in place,

05:15.147 --> 05:16.941
and I send you a little
tax-free donation?

05:17.024 --> 05:19.777
You are gonna cry in agony if
my husband tickles you.

05:19.860 --> 05:22.822
You will plea for your life if
he gives you a back rub.

05:22.905 --> 05:26.116
You will try to escape
just so he can catch you.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.035
Why... would I do that?

05:28.118 --> 05:29.870
Because if you don't,
I will straight-up

05:29.954 --> 05:32.706
just slit your throat.

05:32.790 --> 05:35.000
[chuckles ]
No, no. You wouldn't do that.

05:35.084 --> 05:38.504
- Don't underestimate a woman
in love, Dr. Venture.

05:38.587 --> 05:40.339
So, you allergic
to epinephrine?

05:40.422 --> 05:42.341
No, I'm not
allergic to any anesthetics.

05:42.424 --> 05:44.718
And I'm not allergic
to hand lotion,

05:44.802 --> 05:47.721
if you, uh, want to give me
a happy ending.

05:47.805 --> 05:49.557
Nah.
[crack]

05:49.640 --> 05:50.808
[ Screams ]

05:50.891 --> 05:52.977
Don't start without me!

05:53.060 --> 05:54.979
ACTION MAN: All right. Now, just
like we rehearsed, okay?

05:55.062 --> 05:56.605
That's her.

05:56.689 --> 05:59.483
That delicious piece of randy
candy over there.

05:59.567 --> 06:01.735
