06:01.819 --> 06:04.488
Hello, Rose.
Uh, mind if I --

06:04.572 --> 06:06.782
Yes, I was just leaving anyway.

06:06.866 --> 06:08.993
[Sighs]
Okay,

06:09.076 --> 06:11.620
Oh, dear.
What is the matter?

06:11.704 --> 06:13.831
Oh, it's been a heck
of a year, Rose.

06:13.914 --> 06:16.208
I-I lost my wife,
my best friend,

06:16.292 --> 06:19.545
and now my -- my son is
hooked on rock 'n' roll.

06:19.628 --> 06:20.838
Rock 'n' roll?!

06:20.921 --> 06:22.840
Rodney, that's
the devil's music.

06:22.923 --> 06:24.842
Hey, old man.
I was just playing my bass

06:24.925 --> 06:27.177
at a volume
that's unreasonable.

06:27.261 --> 06:28.888
Can you give me some money
to buy records

06:28.971 --> 06:30.306
With clear warning labels?

06:30.389 --> 06:31.307
Oh, Rose.

06:31.390 --> 06:33.517
You got to help me
straighten him out.

06:33.601 --> 06:36.437
You ain't never gonna stop me
from overly sexualized dancing

06:36.520 --> 06:38.314
and dressing like an indigent.

06:38.397 --> 06:39.565
Loud rock music!

06:39.648 --> 06:41.609
The devil has a grip on you.

06:41.692 --> 06:43.861
You've got to fight him, sweetie.

06:43.944 --> 06:45.988
You have to fight him
with show tunes.

06:46.071 --> 06:48.365
Show tunes?
If I play them backwards,

06:48.449 --> 06:51.035
Will they make me want to try
reefer cigarette marijuanas?

06:51.118 --> 06:52.369
Oh, heaven's no.

06:52.453 --> 06:54.997
They will make you want
to solve problems in song.

06:55.080 --> 06:56.582
And with dancing.

06:56.665 --> 06:59.585
Gosh, I think I'd like
to get hooked on show tunes now.

06:59.668 --> 07:01.670
I've been so wrong about everything.

07:01.754 --> 07:03.672
You're the best father
in the world!

07:03.756 --> 07:05.341
Aw, shucks, son.

07:05.424 --> 07:07.343
I couldn't have done it
without Rose, here.

07:07.426 --> 07:09.136
- You sure do make
a great team.

07:09.219 --> 07:11.138
Hey, Pop, maybe she'd like
to have dinner with us?

07:11.221 --> 07:14.058
Oh, don't be silly.
I'm sure Rose is very --

07:14.141 --> 07:18.020
Oh, yes, young man, I would
love to dine with you.

07:18.103 --> 07:21.190
GENTLEMAN: So, start the watch
when Salem comes on screen,

07:21.273 --> 07:22.733
then stop it when he's off.

07:22.816 --> 07:24.109
Then you write the time down

07:24.193 --> 07:26.070
and indicate whether it was
that crappy puppet

07:26.153 --> 07:28.072
or an actual cat.

07:28.155 --> 07:30.908
Are all these tapes
"Sabrina, The Teenage Witch"?

07:30.991 --> 07:32.034
Well, obviously, son.

07:32.117 --> 07:34.453
It's the only show that starred
Salem the Cat.

07:34.536 --> 07:36.080
Now, once you finish that,

07:36.163 --> 07:38.457
you get to take dictation
for "I Gentleman,"

07:38.540 --> 07:42.503
the third installment of my
autobiographical thrillogy.

07:43.545 --> 07:45.464
GARY: Oh, look at this place.
Nothing changed.

07:45.547 --> 07:46.715
Kept it just the way
I left it.

07:46.799 --> 07:49.051
HATRED:
Hey, how far is the floor from my feet?

07:49.134 --> 07:51.095
Oh, like a yard.

07:51.178 --> 07:52.846
Aw, they got me a Guild
Calamity Conference shirt.

07:52.930 --> 07:54.264
[thud]

07:54.348 --> 07:56.266
Yard.
That was like 5 feet.

07:56.350 --> 07:58.185
Aww, it says
I'm his best henchman.

07:58.268 --> 07:59.603
It's a t-shirt.
So what?

07:59.687 --> 08:01.772
You got any weapons?
- Under the bed.

08:01.855 --> 08:03.774
The Ventures never gave me
a t-shirt.

08:03.857 --> 08:06.402
Boo-hoo.
I tattooed a "V" on my face,

08:06.485 --> 08:08.404
And I still got to pay
for my own food.

08:08.487 --> 08:10.406
Where's your costume?
- Why do you do it?

08:10.489 --> 08:12.908
What? Bodyguard?
It's all the same.

08:12.992 --> 08:15.619
Sergeant Hatred,
Uncle Vatred --

08:15.703 --> 08:17.955
same old war horse fighting
for what he cares about.

08:18.038 --> 08:19.665
Well, what do you
care about?

08:19.748 --> 08:21.291
Fighting.

08:21.375 --> 08:23.293
Yeah, just point me at a cause,
and I'll do the rest.

08:23.377 --> 08:24.795
You know, I can't believe
we're so similar.

08:24.878 --> 08:26.088
How come we never got close?

08:26.171 --> 08:28.924
'Cause I don't trust you,
and 'cause you're a dork.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.426
And this is a toy chest.

08:30.509 --> 08:32.428
- That's a display cabinet
for collectibles, my friend.

08:32.510 --> 08:34.429
It's at the bottom.
That's my old one.

08:34.513 --> 08:36.432
It might still smell
like soup.

08:36.515 --> 08:38.225
[ Grunts ]
That's horrible. What is that?

08:38.308 --> 08:39.518
Soup.

08:39.601 --> 08:42.104
MONARCH:
Okay. I'm so ready.

08:42.187 --> 08:44.023
Let's do this.
- You wanna rehearse again?

08:44.106 --> 08:45.524
No, I got this one down.

08:45.607 --> 08:47.526
You just gotta remember that
after I do the sinister laugh,

08:47.609 --> 08:50.320
cross your arms and look at me
like I'm the shit.

08:50.404 --> 08:52.239
You want me to do the, uh...

08:52.322 --> 08:54.116
No, no.
That's too "King and l."

08:54.199 --> 08:55.951
Keep it believable.
[buzzing lips]

08:56.035 --> 08:58.662
He fights the zeitgeist
with polite might.

08:58.746 --> 09:00.664
[buzzing lips]

09:00.748 --> 09:03.792
[ Inhales]
Okay. Showtime.

09:03.876 --> 09:05.169
[Clank]

09:05.252 --> 09:07.129
Hello, Dr. Venture.

09:07.212 --> 09:10.132
Are you prepared to die?!
- Who's there?

09:10.215 --> 09:11.842
Oh.
Why did you blindfold him?!

09:11.925 --> 09:13.927
I'm all dressed up!

09:15.054 --> 09:17.723
MONARCH:
We Westerners know nothing of torture.

09:17.806 --> 09:19.558
We simply nail a man's balls
to a chair.

09:19.641 --> 09:21.268
Where is the poetry?

09:21.351 --> 09:23.270
Ah, in the East, they know

09:23.353 --> 09:25.105
the exquisite beauty
of torture.

09:25.189 --> 09:27.608
There they've turned a sound
that makes virgins weep

09:27.691 --> 09:30.736
into a sound that makes a man
roar with suffering.

09:30.819 --> 09:33.030
What?
Can't hear squat in here.

09:33.113 --> 09:34.573
Where am I?

09:34.656 --> 09:37.868
The bell!
[laughs maniacally]

09:37.951 --> 09:39.453
DOC:
Labelle? Patti Labelle?

09:39.536 --> 09:41.997
The Bell!
When rung at full peal,

09:42.081 --> 09:44.416
the vibrations pierce the body
like sharp knives

09:44.500 --> 09:47.169
that pull at the muscles
and burst the veins.

09:47.252 --> 09:49.046
The bones twist and crack

09:49.129 --> 09:51.840
in relative silence
to the cries of...

09:51.924 --> 09:52.883
The Bell!

09:52.966 --> 09:55.886
[laughs maniacally]

09:55.969 --> 09:59.056
[bell ringing]
- Right there.

09:59.139 --> 10:00.766
I pay how much to live
in a gated neighborhood,

10:00.849 --> 10:03.769
and some loser cranks
a Mike Oldfield album?

10:03.852 --> 10:05.771
What's next --
Pink Floyd?!

10:05.854 --> 10:11.068
Have another toke, hippie.

10:11.151 --> 10:13.070
What? Nothing?!
Are you serious?

10:13.153 --> 10:14.321
What can I tell you?

10:14.404 --> 10:16.782
I spent most of my childhood
in a supersonic jet.

10:16.865 --> 10:17.991
[ Clears throat]

10:18.075 --> 10:21.078
Oh, I mean, oh!
I think my kidneys burst!

10:21.161 --> 10:23.622
Please, no more bursting
of my... kidneys.

10:23.705 --> 10:27.084
[sighs]
The bell, dot, dot, dot, sucks.

10:27.167 --> 10:30.337
Three exclamation points.

10:30.420 --> 10:32.256
You're finished, Brainulo!

10:32.339 --> 10:34.925
By now, Jonas and Otto have
realigned the missile.

10:35.008 --> 10:36.260
It's over.

10:36.343 --> 10:38.011
You may have bested
my judo lizards,

10:38.095 --> 10:40.931
but you won't fare as well
with your next opponents.

10:41.014 --> 10:43.267
We won't fight each other,
Brainulo!

10:43.350 --> 10:44.893
E-Each other?
Aw...

10:44.977 --> 10:46.770
I wish I thought of that.

10:46.854 --> 10:48.772
Oh, it really seems obvious
now, doesn't it?

10:48.856 --> 10:50.816
- It's all but a cliché, you idiot.

10:50.899 --> 10:52.860
How did you miss that?
- I don't know.

10:52.943 --> 10:55.571
But I did come up with
something more sinister.

10:55.654 --> 10:58.907
Prepare yourself to fight...
your crushes --

10:58.991 --> 11:00.951
Triple Threat
and Jass.

11:01.034 --> 11:03.829
- Nobody for Humongoloid?
- Be realistic, big guy.

11:03.912 --> 11:05.706
You're sweet on Jass, really?

11:05.789 --> 11:06.915
Look at him.

11:06.999 --> 11:08.709
He's like a blade
of sexual grass

11:08.792 --> 11:10.460
swaying in the breeze.

11:10.544 --> 11:12.296
Arrow straight,
believe it or not.

11:12.379 --> 11:14.298
So, Triple Threat?

11:14.381 --> 11:15.841
It's that goody-goody thing.

11:15.924 --> 11:18.427
I just wanna get all animal
on her and show her my filth.

11:18.510 --> 11:20.846
