11:22.556 --> 11:24.141
<i>[ dog barking]
GENTLEMAN: Mischa! Who's that, girl?</i>

11:24.224 --> 11:26.476
ls that Kiki?
ls that Kiki?

11:26.560 --> 11:29.479
That's my puppy.
There's a girl.

11:29.563 --> 11:31.565
[sniffles ]
All right, Dean. Put a pin in that story.

11:31.648 --> 11:33.609
Have to have it out
with Kiki.

11:33.692 --> 11:36.486
That Amber tramp's been
playing me for a fool.

11:36.570 --> 11:39.114
I've been trying to drill Rose
for, like, 40 years.

11:39.198 --> 11:41.116
It's like a damn obsession.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.368
You grease those gears,
and you can name your price.

11:43.452 --> 11:45.746
All right.
I'm gonna need $50 cash,

11:45.829 --> 11:47.581
Stingray bass,
and a ride home,

11:47.664 --> 11:50.542
'cause this whole place smells
like Dinty Moore Beef Stew.

11:50.626 --> 11:53.879
- Done, done, and done.
- Super swear?

11:53.962 --> 11:55.547
If you can get me time
with Rose,

11:55.631 --> 11:59.009
I'll swear on the only thing
holy to me.

11:59.092 --> 12:01.261
TOGETHER:
Go, Team Venture.

12:04.598 --> 12:05.891
<i>21?</i>

12:05.974 --> 12:08.185
Hey, so glad you're back, man.

12:08.268 --> 12:09.895
This place sucks now.
Moppets?

12:09.978 --> 12:11.980
Dude, they're pretty much
running crap in here.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.732
[as #21]
Uh... hello.

12:13.815 --> 12:15.651
What's that blue stuff
on your face?

12:15.734 --> 12:18.612
It's, uh... ice.
Icicles.

12:18.695 --> 12:21.198
[grunts]
W-T-FUCK are you doing?!

12:21.281 --> 12:23.325
You made me hit a guy
on my softball team.

12:23.408 --> 12:26.036
[normal voice]
Yeah, that was -- hey, you saved me.

12:26.119 --> 12:28.914
I didn't think you would.
- Oh, dude, don't get all

12:28.997 --> 12:30.999
Sarah McLachlan dog commercial
on me.

12:31.083 --> 12:34.336
Uh, I'm not, I'm just...
Aww, get over here.

12:34.419 --> 12:35.921
[sighs]
Can we hug later?

12:36.004 --> 12:37.965
You've got to go to the cell
blocks on the lower level.

12:38.048 --> 12:39.925
I'm gonna check the bridge.
- Check.

12:40.008 --> 12:43.387
I won't let you down...
buddy.

12:45.555 --> 12:48.475
Well, isn't that interesting.

12:48.558 --> 12:50.686
[whirring ]
MONARCH: Oh, don't worry.

12:50.769 --> 12:52.479
I'm not going
into that cavity.

12:52.562 --> 12:54.189
That nerve's already dying.

12:54.273 --> 12:57.359
A live, freshly cut nerve is
infinitely more sensitive.

12:57.442 --> 12:59.778
[grunts]
- What?

12:59.861 --> 13:02.114
I can smell your fear.

13:02.197 --> 13:04.908
Ugh, and your fear smells
just like cat food.

13:04.992 --> 13:05.909
Ugh!

13:05.993 --> 13:08.578
Sorry, I had shrimp in garlic
butter last night.

13:08.662 --> 13:11.915
I-I can't -- ugh.
It -- it's just really bad.

13:11.999 --> 13:13.917
How do you even stand
having that be your mouth?

13:14.001 --> 13:16.044
Ugh.
No. No.

13:16.128 --> 13:17.921
GENTLEMAN:
Well, then just get out, then! I'm tired of it.

13:18.005 --> 13:19.589
[ Moroccan accent]
Who this one?

13:19.673 --> 13:21.258
Him new lover
for Mr. Gentleman?

13:21.341 --> 13:22.759
That's my son.

13:22.843 --> 13:25.095
Are you leaving, or should
I throw you out?

13:25.178 --> 13:28.056
No. Kiki leave.
Kiki have new man.

13:28.140 --> 13:30.058
Great! Have fun.

13:30.142 --> 13:31.727
Maybe when he kicks
his coke habit,

13:31.810 --> 13:35.772
your new man will kick you
like he does all his boys!

13:38.483 --> 13:41.361
I... um... I arranged
the first two chapters for you

13:41.445 --> 13:43.947
and then made a chapter
for your lists.

13:44.031 --> 13:46.950
Yes. Yes, let's get back
to my lists.

13:47.034 --> 13:48.827
If you want to talk
about this --

13:48.910 --> 13:51.663
Colonel Gentleman's List
of Things Not to Do.

13:51.747 --> 13:55.000
Number one -- get involved
with a person 1/3 your age.

13:55.083 --> 13:56.752
You hear me, Dean?

13:56.835 --> 14:00.297
Uh, I can safely promise that I won't
get involved with a 6-year-old.

14:00.380 --> 14:02.341
Number two --
retire to a country

14:02.424 --> 14:05.093
where your sexual preference
is a capital offense.

14:05.177 --> 14:07.763
Number three --
stay past your welcome.

14:07.846 --> 14:10.015
This place used to be
a paradise.

14:10.098 --> 14:12.017
That pretty peacock
Yves Saint Laurent

14:12.100 --> 14:13.810
lived right there.

14:13.894 --> 14:17.272
Burroughs, Capote, Forbes,
Kerouac, Ginsberg --

14:17.356 --> 14:20.317
ah, Ginsberg,
that eager little puppy.

14:20.400 --> 14:21.985
I miss 'em.

14:22.069 --> 14:24.988
They're all gone, Dean.
And here I am.

14:25.072 --> 14:26.573
Should I be writing
this down?

14:26.656 --> 14:28.533
Yes, but not for my memoirs.

14:28.617 --> 14:31.036
For me, so I can look
at my life.

14:31.119 --> 14:33.997
What am I doing here?

14:34.081 --> 14:35.916
<i>Doc'?</i>

14:35.999 --> 14:38.001
Psst. Doc?
You in here?

14:38.085 --> 14:39.836
[gun cocks]
MOPPET: Looking for someone?

14:39.920 --> 14:41.046
Where's Doc?

14:41.129 --> 14:44.174
He's being tortured
by The Monarch and 21.

14:44.257 --> 14:46.385
You're such a sucker, man.

14:46.468 --> 14:49.054
Fat boy been playing you
the whole time.

14:49.137 --> 14:51.390
He would never --
you're lying!

14:51.473 --> 14:53.392
Whatever.
Show this man out...

14:53.475 --> 14:56.895
and treat him appropriately --
use the garbage chute.

14:56.978 --> 14:59.231
[yells]

14:59.314 --> 15:01.483
Show me the garbage chute,
will you?

15:01.566 --> 15:03.151
You're the garbage here!

15:03.235 --> 15:06.863
You're a bunch of lying...
garbage people.

15:07.864 --> 15:09.866
Where the hell is everybody?

15:09.950 --> 15:12.494
Well, hello, traitor.

15:12.577 --> 15:14.663
Security to the throne room.

15:14.746 --> 15:16.498
Well, look who it is.

15:16.581 --> 15:19.209
Yeah, I was tipped off
by your new best friend.

15:19.292 --> 15:20.877
I gave him Dr. Venture

15:20.961 --> 15:23.046
and he sold you out
like you were nothing,

15:23.130 --> 15:24.256
so why don't you
put these on

15:24.339 --> 15:26.383
and we'll go have
a chat with The Monarch?

15:26.466 --> 15:28.218
All right, yeah.
Let's.

15:28.301 --> 15:30.679
Let's show him how you two are
taking over the cocoon.

15:30.762 --> 15:32.139
He'll never believe you.

15:32.222 --> 15:34.474
Oh, he'll believe his
best henchman

15:34.558 --> 15:37.519
over a lying murderer.

15:37.602 --> 15:39.146
I know it was you guys.

15:39.229 --> 15:41.064
[ Door opens ]

15:41.148 --> 15:42.315
Seize the traitor!

15:42.399 --> 15:45.652
Wait! The Moppets have
broken our most sacred law.

15:45.735 --> 15:50.240
They killed henchman 24.
Hench has killed hench.

15:50.323 --> 15:52.492
Hench has killed hench.
Hench has killed hench.

15:52.576 --> 15:55.287
ALL: [chanting]
Hench has killed hench...

15:55.370 --> 15:57.414
We didn't!
He's a liar and a traitor!

15:57.497 --> 15:59.416
Seize him!
- ALL: Hench has killed hench.

15:59.499 --> 16:03.003
I can prove he's lying.
Idiots! He's getting away!

16:04.463 --> 16:06.798
[ Sighs ]
Forget it.

16:06.882 --> 16:09.092
We looked everywhere for that
goddamn extension cord.

16:09.176 --> 16:11.511
I'm done. I'm done.
- What are you doing?

16:11.595 --> 16:14.014
I'm untying you
and letting you go.

16:14.097 --> 16:16.099
About time
Team Venture rescued me.

16:16.183 --> 16:17.559
Nobody came
to rescue you.

16:17.642 --> 16:19.311
Look, nobody even answered
my ransom calls.

16:19.394 --> 16:21.104
Well, maybe if you
hold me longer.

16:21.188 --> 16:22.898
I -- I'm sure somebody's
working on a rescue plan.

16:22.981 --> 16:25.901
Forget it. We lose.
We're wash-ups. Losers.

16:25.984 --> 16:28.028
You know my best henchman
left me?

16:28.111 --> 16:30.030
Yeah. He's been hanging
around my place.

16:30.113 --> 16:32.115
That wouldn't have happened
if Brock was still around.

16:32.199 --> 16:34.576
Be happy you don't have
dwarves taking over your life.

16:34.659 --> 16:37.037
[ Scoffs ]
You haven't met my brother, apparently.

16:37.120 --> 16:38.872
Oh, yeah.
He's really doing well, huh?

16:38.955 --> 16:40.457
Yeah, I have that
with my wife.

16:40.540 --> 16:42.000
She was just tapped for the
Council of 13,

16:42.083 --> 16:45.337
so my old number two
will be my boss.

16:45.420 --> 16:46.922
That's nothing.

16:47.005 --> 16:48.590
My new bodyguard is
my old archenemy.

16:48.673 --> 16:50.592
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, that's messed up.

16:50.675 --> 16:53.178
All right. Well...
Guess you should just go home.

16:53.261 --> 16:54.679
Can you even call it
a home?

16:54.763 --> 16:56.181
Is it just a box full
of memories?

16:56.264 --> 16:57.849
All right.
Um... can I get a ride?

16:57.933 --> 16:59.518
No, no. Can't.

16:59.601 --> 17:01.186
I gotta tell the wife
you escaped and...

17:01.269 --> 17:02.479
well, you understand.

17:02.562 --> 17:04.314
Yeah, no.
So, uh... should I just...

17:04.396 --> 17:06.191
Yeah, let yourself out.

17:06.273 --> 17:09.069
Uh, break a couple of things.
Make it look good.

17:09.152 --> 17:11.988
God. I liked being tortured
more than this here.

17:12.071 --> 17:15.325
This is... ugh.

17:15.407 --> 17:18.203
I'm just so damn lonely, Rose.

17:18.286 --> 17:19.621
Let's give it a shot.

17:19.704 --> 17:21.540
We're just too different, Rodney.

17:21.623 --> 17:23.708
You're a womanizer
and a junkie.

17:23.791 --> 17:25.417
Oh, no.
That all ended.

17:25.502 --> 17:28.463
I was faithful to Jeannie
'til the day she died.

17:28.547 --> 17:31.216
And junkie?
I-l was a dang super soldier.

17:31.299 --> 17:32.551
Jonas had me on jump juice

17:32.634 --> 17:34.219
for the good of flag
and country.

17:34.302 --> 17:35.887
I kicked that years ago.

17:35.971 --> 17:39.182
Rodney, that's just a bushel
of baloney.

17:39.266 --> 17:41.560
[gasps]
Wait a minute. That voice!

17:41.643 --> 17:44.604
I-I finally figured out
why you're so familiar.

17:44.688 --> 17:46.231
Do you have a son
named Billy?

17:46.314 --> 17:48.191
Uh, big head, eye patch,
metal hand,

17:48.275 --> 17:49.818
probably a midget?

17:49.901 --> 17:52.654
Yes.
Oh, my little water baby.

17:52.737 --> 17:54.656
Oh, I haven't seen him
in years.

17:54.739 --> 17:56.366
He moved in with a man.

17:56.449 --> 17:58.660
I think he was afraid
I'll disapprove of his...

17:58.743 --> 18:00.453
lifestyle choice.

18:00.537 --> 18:02.581
I don't even know
where he is anymore.

18:02.664 --> 18:04.541
Well, I do.
He's my neighbor.

18:04.624 --> 18:07.711
Hey, how about you two
come visit me back home?

18:07.794 --> 18:09.796
You and Uncle Rodney
and my new bass

18:09.879 --> 18:13.800
and your little water baby
can have a nice reunion.

18:13.883 --> 18:16.970
Yes. Well, that sounds
just elegant.

