18:25.312 --> 18:27.230
HATRED:
All right, Gary.

18:27.314 --> 18:29.691
Judas. Betray me, will you?

18:29.774 --> 18:32.527
Oh, ho, a reckoning's coming, buddy.

18:32.611 --> 18:35.238
A reckoning is coming!

18:37.782 --> 18:39.826
Sweetie, Dr. Venture escaped!

18:39.909 --> 18:42.287
No, he didn't.
I let him go.

18:42.370 --> 18:45.582
What? Are you okay?
Why did you let him go?

18:45.665 --> 18:47.876
Because I broke him!

18:47.959 --> 18:51.171
I broke his will!
I broke his spirit.

18:51.254 --> 18:53.048
Oh, my lovely,
naive little girl,

18:53.131 --> 18:55.175
how easy it is
to break a bone,

18:55.258 --> 18:58.720
but to break a man's heart --
that takes genius.

18:58.803 --> 19:01.097
Physical torture?
Wounds heal.

19:01.181 --> 19:02.724
But mental torture?

19:02.807 --> 19:05.977
Those wounds only grow
and fester.

19:06.061 --> 19:08.855
I have crushed
Dr. Venture!

19:08.938 --> 19:12.651
[laughs maniacally]

19:12.734 --> 19:16.112
You know I'm the shit!
- I am so turned on.

19:16.196 --> 19:17.864
You have to do me
right now.

19:17.947 --> 19:20.283
Come.
Service your evil genius.

19:20.367 --> 19:22.869
[ Door opens ]
Oh, uh... hey, you guys

19:22.952 --> 19:24.871
I'm, uh... I'm home?

19:24.954 --> 19:26.706
HATRED:
<i>Attention, Gary.</i>

19:26.790 --> 19:29.501
It's your old pal,
Sergeant Hatred.

19:29.584 --> 19:32.629
Come out with your hands up,
or I will --

19:32.712 --> 19:34.631
Oh. Oh, that's a missile.

19:34.714 --> 19:37.467
Oh, boy.
That is on all kinds of fire.

19:37.550 --> 19:40.303
It's heading for the house
and it is on fire.

19:40.387 --> 19:41.763
Gary, I still hate you,

19:41.846 --> 19:43.473
but you gotta get out
of there!

19:43.556 --> 19:45.809
You got to evacuate, man!

19:48.478 --> 19:50.563
Oh, the humanity!

19:50.647 --> 19:52.607
I-I'm just gonna go now
and, uh...

19:52.691 --> 19:54.859
we'll pick this up
another time.

19:54.943 --> 19:58.488
[coughs]
What the fuck was that?

19:58.571 --> 20:00.490
Our cocoon.

20:00.573 --> 20:03.368
[coughs]
That sucked.

20:03.451 --> 20:05.412
Who the fuck is Gary?

20:05.495 --> 20:07.580
[ Up-tempo music plays]

20:33.523 --> 20:36.067
[ car doors close ]

20:36.151 --> 20:38.069
MRS. MONARCH:
Oh, it's so romantic.

20:38.153 --> 20:40.029
We're moving into the house
you were raised in.

20:40.113 --> 20:41.531
It's like a fairy tale.

20:41.614 --> 20:43.700
Uh, it didn't look quite this
bad when I was a kid.

20:43.783 --> 20:45.493
Yeah, it looks like
the kind of place

20:45.577 --> 20:48.371
that has creepy, wet Asian kids
crawling on the ceiling.

20:48.455 --> 20:51.166
He's a lying, two-timing
little so-and-so,

20:51.249 --> 20:52.751
and I broke bread with him!

20:52.834 --> 20:54.377
I even broke heads with him.

20:54.461 --> 20:56.045
You can't
take it personally.

20:56.129 --> 20:57.714
Oh, just watch me!

20:57.797 --> 20:59.591
Just play along.
It's not gonna kill you.

20:59.674 --> 21:01.551
Why would you
tell your mom I'm gay?

21:01.634 --> 21:03.511
I didn't tell her.
I just didn't deny it.

21:03.595 --> 21:05.680
She sent us that China
and the sideboard.

21:05.764 --> 21:07.432
White, you love
that sideboard.

21:07.515 --> 21:09.476
So, this is Peter.

21:09.559 --> 21:11.644
He's as handsome as you said
he was, Billy.

21:11.728 --> 21:13.480
You said I was handsome?

21:13.563 --> 21:16.608
Yeah, it's a little brownstone
on Christopher Street.

21:16.691 --> 21:18.651
You can bring Rose.
What do you say?

21:18.735 --> 21:21.404
If you don't mind the sound
of old people having sex,

21:21.488 --> 21:24.407
you've got yourself
a roommate.

21:24.491 --> 21:26.576
Dean, you look like
someone died.

21:26.659 --> 21:27.994
This is a funeral, Hank.

21:28.077 --> 21:30.288
No, I mean, like,
all the time.

21:30.371 --> 21:32.415
You've been a mess
this whole year, man.

21:32.499 --> 21:34.000
You've got to tell me
what's eating you.

21:34.083 --> 21:36.336
You want to know, Hank?
Okay, fine.

21:36.419 --> 21:38.713
I'm sick of keeping it in,
so I'll just tell you.

21:38.797 --> 21:42.550
[sighs]
We... are... clones, Hank.

21:42.634 --> 21:44.552
Our whole lives --
it's a lie.

21:44.636 --> 21:47.430
We're not really Hank and Dean anymore.

21:47.514 --> 21:48.890
We've died like 13 times,

21:48.973 --> 21:51.434
and now we're copies of ourselves.

21:51.518 --> 21:53.019
We're clones.

21:53.102 --> 21:55.355
Clones.

21:55.438 --> 21:58.650
Dean...
that is awesome.

21:58.733 --> 21:59.901
You're --
you're not upset?

21:59.984 --> 22:01.444
About what?!

22:01.528 --> 22:03.071
That I'm, like,
some kind of super-cool,

22:03.154 --> 22:05.740
probably magic,
Highlander cyborg clone?!

22:05.824 --> 22:07.033
Uh, no.

22:07.116 --> 22:10.537
Hey, just one more reason
it's great to be a Venture.

22:12.580 --> 22:13.998
ACTION MAN:
Goodbye, old friend.

22:14.082 --> 22:17.502
Hope you're happy
in your new resting place.

22:17.585 --> 22:20.338
Okay, who's the youngest?

22:20.421 --> 22:21.798
Don't look at me.

22:21.881 --> 22:24.467
Dean, son!
We need you over here.

22:24.551 --> 22:26.970
Oh, you're gonna love this.

